legacy.full_text:
China is focused on development. The goal of the governing party and the government of China is to meet the growing needs of the Chinese people for a better life. 
We have no interest to rival or overtake the superpower for dominance. We export goods, not political system. https://t.co/UGfOL0vJ1M
A few points about China's position on the #Ukraine Situation. https://t.co/Afy2NSOFNW

Perspective4⃣: We are for win-win economic cooperation. China needs the world, needs Europe, needs the NL, and vice versa. It is in our mutual interest to work for double wins. https://t.co/BT8y5gP6qv

Perspective3⃣: We hope that Europe could move beyond the "partner-competitor-rival" characterization of its relations with China. Highlighting systemic rivalry may rock the boat of🇨🇳🇪🇺relations. We have more common interests;no fundamental conflict of interest. 
We are partners. https://t.co/uzdfOpruiS
Perspective2⃣: Competition should be fair. It can't be "heads I win tails you cheat". https://t.co/o4fc0dlmhr

When celebrating the accomplishments of our bilateral relations, we're fully aware of &will not hide from the challenges. How we see them? Here are some of the perspectives from our side. 

Perspective1⃣: Those accusations of China's human rights violation are not fact-based. https://t.co/pgxigeW5SS

This year 2022 is special, because it marks the 50th anniversary of the establishment of our diplomatic relations. Beside me on the stage is the logo for the anniversary, of which I'd like to give you a brief introduction. https://t.co/TmxK8JIJJ2

Some excerpts from my speech at the Witheerenlezing event on March 22. 

First of all, about my impression of the Netherlands, a country with global footage and full of vitality. https://t.co/K2mSsb1XWd

Glad to speak at the Witheerenlezing event on China-Netherlands relations and interact with audience. 

Read the full text of my remarks: 
https://t.co/zesTPuQJid https://t.co/spm2EWyXNp

My great pleasure to join PM Rutte & Minister Helder at the ceremony for 🇳🇱medalists of #Beijing2022 today.
My warmest congratulations to all athletes & utmost respect to your passion, dedication & Olympic spirit. And I wish Beijing will always be part of your memory. https://t.co/TUv50M1iNK

legacy.full_text:
Happy New Year!🎊
On the last day of 2021, my interview with De Telegraaf @telegraaf is published. Welcome to read the full text of the transcript of the interview here 👉https://t.co/ijsWHlJfoy.
Wish you all a happy and prosperous 2022!
https://t.co/VlIDTxFCLD

A very pleasant trip to Eindhoven last Friday. Impressed by the innovative city, the brainport of NL. 
Also my great honor to deliver a speech at the opening of Nanjing Pavilion & unveil the name of this symbol of friendship together with Mayor @JJorritsma040. https://t.co/XxssvIdN8N

Thanks to @aardsbevlogen @KeijserA and @SilviaMarijnis1, after 13 years of their hard work, the first Dutch translation of The Dream of the Red Chamber, one of China's Four Great Classical Novels, will be published soon! This is indeed a milestone in the 🇨🇳🇳🇱cultural exchange. https://t.co/gHt0du5OZF

My article published by Diplomat Magazine on the occasion of the 100-day countdown to #Beijing2022. Let’s meet in Beijing, together for a shared future! Full text https://t.co/alkxijMT3k https://t.co/jfGsBULjo7

My great pleasure to deliver remarks at the Netherlands - Hong Kong Friendship Dinner yesterday. We believe HK's future will only be brighter. And as I said in my remarks, int'l cooperation is more needed today than ever. China is part of the solution, not part of the problem. https://t.co/P9DZAT2oeS
Read full text of my remarks here👉https://t.co/RFztft9uCc
